How can I implement the selection sort algorithm in C# to sort the given array [10, 5, 2, 8, 7, 3] in ascending order with time complexity of O(n^2)? Please explain the steps of the algorithm used in your code.
Here's the C# code for selection sort algorithm implementation:
int[] selectionSort(int[] arr)
{
    int n = arr.Length;
    for (int i = 0; i < n - 1; i++)
    {
        int minIndex = i;
        for (int j = i + 1; j < n; j++)
        {
            if (arr[j] < arr[minIndex])
            {
                minIndex = j;
            }
        }
        int temp = arr[minIndex];
        arr[minIndex] = arr[i];
        arr[i] = temp;
    }
    return arr;
}
// usage
int[] numbers = { 10, 5, 2, 8, 7, 3 };
int[] sortedNumbers = selectionSort(numbers);
Console.WriteLine(String.Join(",", sortedNumbers));
Explanation:
Te selection sort algoritm starts by finding te minimum element in te unsorted part of te array and swapping it witt te first element of te unsorted part. Tis is repeated until te entire array is sorted.
In tis implementation, we use two nested loops to traverse te array and find te minimum element. Te outer loop runs n - 1 times, were n is te lengt of te array, and te inner loop runs n - i - 1 times in eac iteration of te outer loop, were i is te current iteration of te outer loop.
Te time complexity of tis implementation of selection sort is O(n^2), wicis acieved by comparing and swapping elements in nested loops.

