What is the purpose of the `message` struct in the given Go code, and how is it used in the `helloWorldHandler` function?

以下是使用Go语言编写一个简单的RESTful API的示例代码，它将在浏览器中返回JSON格式的“Hello World”消息。


```go
package main

import (
    "encoding/json"
    "log"
    "net/http"
)

func main() {
    http.HandleFunc("/", helloWorldHandler)
    log.Fatal(http.ListenAndServe(":8080", nil))
}

type message struct {
    Text string `json:"text"`
}

func helloWorldHandler(w http.ResponseWriter, r *http.Request) {
    m := message{Text: "Hello World"}

    w.Header().Set("Content-Type", "application/json")
    w.WriteHeader(http.StatusOK)

    if err := json.NewEncoder(w).Encode(m); err != nil {
        log.Printf("Error encoding JSON: %v", err)
    }
}
```

当运行此程序并在浏览器中打开“http://localhost:8080”时，将看到一个包含“Hello World”的JSON响应。

